This show was a Live-To-Air broadcast, presented by Anita Alphabet & Test Pattern. This was a 3RRR subscriber and doorlist only event. Eyes Like the Sky contained an extra verse; "In the life and adventures of M. O’Brian. Scout, pioneer, gunfighter and Yavapai warrior...". After Evil Man, Ambrose dedicated the set to the Kernaghan family. The live broadcast ended after 30 Past 7, but the band played Let Me Mend The Past, Mystery Jack, and God Is Calling Me Back Home to finish the set. God Is Calling Me Back Home contained a false start. After Mystery Jack, Stu said that they had to cut the set short due to Cookie and Ambrose having band practice for the Murlocs. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is now complete. Thank you to 3RRR for sharing their archived recording of this performance. If anyone has any further information about this show, please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.
